The senatorial race in Vihiga county has gained momentum after four aspirants lined up to replace the incumbent George Khaniri, who is running for governor. Khaniri was first elected senator in 2013 on UDF party. In 2017, he was reelected on the ANC ticket. Those seeking to succeed Khaniri include nominated MP Godfrey Osotsi, Jackson Swadi (MCA Kabwareng ward, Nandi county), Babira Ndeda and Leo Ongadi. Osotsi will vie for the seat on an ODM ticket while Ongadi is likely to join the DAP-K party. Ongadi previously worked as  a project manager in the States. Speaking to​​ The Star Osotsi said he is the best candidate for Vihiga Senator. "If I am elected I will ensure we have proper oversight in Vihiga county," he said. "I ensure resources of this county are well utilised," Osotsi added. Swadi pledge that under his leadership he will ensure devolution is fully protected. Khaniri has challenged the aspirants seeking to succeed him to focus on selling their agenda to the residents.